@NODE "Prefs"

  akPNGPrefs
  -----------
  akPNGPrefs is the Preferences Program for akPNG.datatype.

  GUI has been designed with StormWizard 2.0, so this program needs
  "wizard.library" V42+ (you can find a copy on Aminet under
  "biz/haage/WizardLibrary.lha" or even never versions under
  ftp.haage-partner.com).

  Icon by Bert Bosma <lmb@wxs.nl> (based on NewIcons).

  Task (process) specific settings also can be done - either using
  the preferences program (which allows to select the corresponding
  process from a list as long as it actually is running at the same
  time) or by hand, following the scheme below:

                           OPTIONAL
  ---------------- task specific settings files -----------------------
  Settings specific to different caller programs may be created
  by copying the global settings from "Datatypes/akPNG.prefs" to an
  optional task-related prefs file called

            "Datatypes/akPNG.prefs_Tasks/TaSkNaMe"

  where "TaSkNaMe" means the name of the program as e.g. shown by
  a system monitor (for obvious reasons, this does work best with
  workbench programs, which don't require name patterns as some
  CLI programs might do, like for example "CLI(3):Work:Browsers/XWebber").
  So, with AWeb for example, you would just edit your global settings
  file and then do the following:

    MakeDir ENV:Datatypes/akPNG.prefs_Tasks
    Copy ENV:Datatypes/akPNG.prefs ENV:Datatypes/akPNG.prefs_Tasks/AWebIP"

     [... and the same for ENVARC: ...]

  After that, AWeb will ignore the global settings and fetch its own
  from the given file.
  ---------------------------------------------------------------------

  Public options (available via prefs program):

   STRIPALPHA=<ON|OFF>          => see prefs program
   SWAPALPHA=<ON|OFF>           => see prefs program
   TRANSTOALPHA=<ON|OFF>        => see prefs program

  Hidden options (not available via prefs program):

   NO_V43_IN_8BIT               => compatibility option,
                                   by default active for ReqAttack
   CUSTOM_MODES=<0x...hexID...> => use a fixed viewmode always
   NOASPECT                     => use fixed 1:1 aspect always
                                   (no calculation, faster)
   DEBUG                        => enable debug mode (output)

  WARNING: if the pic-dt of your OS version does not support
           alpha channel handling, then always set STRIPALPHA=ON
           (no ARGB/RGBA)

@ENDNODE

@NODE "History"

 History
 =======
 V45.95 (30.12.2008):  - removed MOS support, as there are more
                         frequent MOS updates now and as there still
                         is no fully featured new SDK for external 
                         developers; makes semi-redundant datatype
                         development finally quite pointless
                       - copyright bump

 V45.90 (13.9.2008):   - upgraded to libpng 1.2.31;
                         which fixes a number of security
                         issues and possible crashes
                       - MOS 1.4.5 no longer supported;
                         now testing using MOS 2.0 (2.1)

 V45.89 (27.6.2008):   - updated TestDTAlpha tool and check for
                         PICDTALPHA

                       - upgraded to libpng 1.2.29;
                         which fixes a number of security
                         issues and possible crashes

 V45.88 (20.1.2008):   - added TestDTAlpha tool and check for
                         PICDTALPHA

 V45.87 (7.1.2008):    - fixed version/date strings for V45.86
                       - fixed the viewmode fix from V45.86
                         a second time

 V45.86 (5.1.2008):    - fixed long-standing MOS bug in viewmode
                         generation routine (did not occur with 68k
                         and did only pop up with some graphics)

 V45.85 (4.1.2008):    - MOS/68k: now really building from same
                                  source tree; the following
                                  information is relative to
                                  the former MOS tree
                       - reduced memory consumption for 8 bit (68k)
                       - fixed minor one-time mem-leak caused
                         by V45.83 changes
                       - improved MOS startup code
                       - finally removed dithering settings code
                       - removed some obsolete prefs settings
                       - documented all prefs settings again
                         in the @{"Prefs" LINK Prefs} section
                       - Prefs: made the labels easier to understand,
                                especially the alpha settings

 V45.84 (2.1.2008):    - Copyright bump to 2008
                       - optimized the mem-leak fix from V45.83
                       - MOS: added some 68k optimizations also here
                       - some additions to asyncio routines
                       - improvements in asyncio routines

 V45.83 (28.12.2007):  - fixed bug in asyncio dispatcher, which
                         could have lead to a stale file lock,
                         thus memory loss, in case of DOS fallback
                         during AsyncIO availability
                       - added missing pointer null-ing in one
                         of the decoders
                       - added easy workaround for what seems
                         to be a bunch of memory leaks and/or
                         buffer trashes in libpng (.18 and .24)

                       - upgraded to libpng 1.2.24

 V45.82 (26.12.2007):  - minor optimization in dispatcher

 V45.81 (12.10.2007):  - if you at first do not succeed...

 V45.80 (6.10.2007):   - for some types of images PDTA_DestMode
                         was set to PMODE_V43 by the dt itself,
                         but not reset afterwards (no idea, if
                         a reset is possible at all, but this
                         now is at least tried)

 V45.79 (5.10.2007):   - Guide: - v45.78 history was missing

                       - enhanced async/normal IO dispatcher
                       - asyncio now also used for temp files

 V45.78 (2.10.2007):   - Prefs: - added "Reset" option for
                                  default settings

 V45.77 (29.9.2007):   - Prefs: if stripalpha is on, the other
                                two options now are disabled

                         WARNING: if the pic-dt of your OS
                                  version does not support
                                  alpha channel handling,
                                  then always set STRIP_ALPHA=ON
                                  (no ARGB/RGBA)

 V45.76 (23.9.2007):   - 68k: fixed ReqAttach task name check

                       - 68k: TRANSTOALPHA setting now ignored
                              for ReqAttack (remains 8 bit)
                       - MOS: TRANSTOALPHA setting now ignored
                              for ReqAttack (remains 8 bit)

 V45.75 (5.8.2007):    - merged V45.71 - V45.74 history;
                         reverted some of the changes therein

                       - fixed some possible issue with tasknames
                         shorter than 3 characters (if any?)
                       - STRIPALPHA was not working anymore,
                         reverted the change from V45.66 which
                         caused the problem (could have caused
                         partially garbaged display, maybe also
                         MungWall hits - not on my system though)
                         (-> Thomas Klein)
                       - prior to reading from a V43 bitmap, it
                         must be explicitely put to V43 mode again(?)
                         (P96 pic-dt V43 specific; AmiKit)
                       - removed some more legacy code

                       - 68k: NO_V43_IN_8BIT is back and by default
                              active for ReqAttack#? tasks (not
                              recommended)

                       - Prefs: fixed STRIPALPHA gadget bug

 V45.70 (1.8.2007):    - 68k: removed all V40 legacy code
                       - 68k: will not run with pic-dt < V43 anymore
                       - 68k: removed 24 bit -> 8 bit dithering
                       - 68k: removed 24 bit -> HAM 6/8 conversion
                       - 68k: removed all V40-related settings

                       - memory-related optimizations

                       - Prefs: removed all V40-related settings
                       - Prefs: will not run with pic-dt < V43 anymore
                       - Prefs: will not run with wizard-lib < V42 anymore

 V45.66 (28.7.2007):   - address change

                       - updated german .guide file

                       - removed duplicate read_update_info()
                       - adding missing DOS error code (fileype check)
                       - fixed some file recognition issue (should
                         not have bothered anyone, since redundant)
                       - some minor improvements
                       - fixed wrong clean-up order for some error
                         cases (rare occurance)

                       - 68k: added two missing DOS error codes for
                              the V40 "with multiple channels" case
                       - 68k: now uses V43 API also in V40-fallback
                              mode for 8 bit, as long as pic-dt is V43
                       - 68k: now uses V43 API also in V40-fallback
                              mode for 24->8 bit,
                              as long as pic-dt is V43
                       - 68k: significant speedup for V43 systems,
                              as long as enough memory is available,
                              otherwise fallback to slower code
                       - 68k: added undocumented NO_V43_IN_8BIT
                              switch which disables the new
                              optimizations
                       - 68k: note, that HAM6/8 mode has not been
                              V43 speed-optimized yet

 V45.63 (3.6.2007):    - reduced size of all 68k versions by ca. 5kb
                       - optimized error handling
                       - killed some (partially dead) references
                         to standard C library
                       - optimized prefs parsing under MOS, too

 V45.62 (25.6.2007):   - fixed v45.61 history
                       - analyzed memory usage
                       - memory allocation routine now adapts itself
                         better to system config (pool adjustment)
                       - optimized pool configuration in general

 V45.61 (23.5.2007):   - 68k: improved interlaced reading on machines
                         with little RAM and no AsyncIO
                       - MOS: former 020+ C code now enabled for PPC
                       - upgraded to libpng 1.2.18

 V45.60 (29.4.2007):   - prefs program now creates env "tasks" dir
                         prior to saving task-specific prefs
                         (-> Bernd Roesch)

 V45.58 (3.3.2007):    - added new undocumented setting, which
                         allows to swap the alpha value from
                         ARGB to RGBA if set (SWAPALPHA=ON);
                         the resulting bitmap will be of that type

 V45.57 (13.1.2007):   - MOS dt version ID still was 45.52 (updated)
                       - removed old workaround, which always
                         increased a depth of 1 to a depth of 2
                       - do not set interleaved flag when allocating
                         bitmaps of depth 1
                       - upgraded to libpng 1.2.15

 V45.55 (26.11.2006):  - updated installer
                       - minor fixes in .guide
                       - fixed problem with asyncio and truncated
                         or broken files

 V45.52 (10.9.2006):   - fixed problem with missing DEBUG switch
                         in Prefs and debug output always
                         being written to T:

 V45.51 (31.8.2006):   - INOFFICIAL BETA
                       - now uses memory pools (68k + MOS)
                         also for libpng-internal allocations;
                         fixes some rare crash situations under
                         MorphOS and with FBlit under 68k
                         (obviously race conditions or alike)
                         (-> Luca Longone, for the latter)

